**Any of the provided code can be modified to suit the needs of an individual or organization**

1. Copy or download script to desired system with powershell and Active Directory module installed

2. Right Click on script 

3. Press 'y' if prompted to allow script to run

4. Enter the IP address of the AD server you'd like to connect to and make changes 

5. Enter your credentials for that domain

6. Enter the name of the user you're searching for (Note that this shouldn't be the sAMAccountName but the value in the display name field) 

7. Follow prompts
